CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 9, 1960, pg. 2, reads: "New Year's First Citizen - Nurse Georgina Dietrich holds the first infant to be born in Pittsburgh after the arrival of 1960. The tiny girl, daughter of Mrs. Carol Alvarez of 712 Anaheim St., came into the world two minute after midnight at Magee Hospital. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Nurse Georgina Dietrich holding infant daughter of Carol Alvarez
